node.title: Ko endures horror first round at US Open
node.description: Lydia Ko's endured a horror opening round at the US Golf Open at Pebble Beach, in California.
node.content:
["", "
Lydia Ko. Photo: PHOTOSPORT
", "Lydia Ko's endured a horror opening round at the US Golf Open at Pebble Beach, in California.", "New Zealand's world number three had a quadruple bogey on the par three fifth hole and two further bogeys to finish 4-over 76, nine shots off the lead.", "She wasn't alone however in struggling.", "World No. 1 Jin Young Ko of South Korea finished with a 7-over 79 and World No. 2 Nelly Korda was at 4-over 76 alongside Ko.", "Xiyu "Janet" Lin of China and Hyo Joo Kim of South Korea are tied at the top of the leaderboard at 4-under 68.", "Lin, the World No. 9, is the highest-ranked player without a win on the LPGA Tour.", "Her counterpart, Kim, is ranked No. 8 in the world and won her first and only major title at the 2014 Evian Championship.", "The third major of the women's golf season is offering up a record $US11 million purse, with $US2 million to the winner.", "Michelle Wie West, in the final event of her playing career, opened with a 79.", "-RNZ/Reuters"]
